{{nihongo|'''''Messenger of Allah'''''|アラーの使者|Arā no Shisha}} is a Japanese [[tokusatsu]] TV series produced by [[Toei Company]] starring a young [[Sonny Chiba]], at the time known as Shin'ichi Chiba.<ref name="画報">{{cite book|title=超人画報―国産架空ヒーロー四十年の歩み (Chōjin Gahō Kokusan Kakū Hīrō Yon Jū-nen no Ayumi)|date=November 30, 1995|publisher=株式会社竹書房 (Takeshobo Co.Ltd.)|location=Japan|isbn=4-88475-874-9|page=48}}</ref> It was created by writer [[Kōhan Kawauchi|Yasunori Kawauchi]], who was also responsible for creating ''[[Moonlight Mask]]'' and ''[[Seven Color Mask]]''. The series ran from July 7, 1960 to December 27, 1960 on [[TV Asahi|NET]] (now TV Asahi) for a total of 26 episodes.

==Development==
After [[Seven Color Mask|''New Seven Color Mask'']] ended its run, Shin'ichi Chiba continued on to star in Yasunori Kawauchi's swashbuckler adventure ''Messenger of Allah''.<ref name = "画報"/> The title character was also the basis for [[Rainbowman|''Warrior of Love Rainbowman'']],<ref name = "画報"/> which Kawauchi also created and wrote for, and also aired on NET.<ref>{{cite book|last=岩佐 (Iwasa)|first=陽一 (Yoichi)|title=70年代カルトTV図鑑 (70-Nendai Karuto TV zukan)|date=Apr 2001|publisher=Bungeishunjū Ltd.|location=Japan|isbn=978-4167660154|page=18}}</ref> The film for the first episode is all that exists,<ref name="60年代">{{cite book|author=石橋春海|date=2013-12-05|title='60年代 蘇る昭和特撮ヒーロー (60-Nendai Yomigaeru Shōwa Tokusatsu Hīrō)|publisher=コスミック出版 (Cosmic Publication)|series=COSMIC MOOK|pages=66|ISBN=978-4-7747-5853-4 }}</ref> which can be found on the Toei Tokusatsu BB website.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140515155240/https://www.tokusatsu.jp/ Toei Tokusatsu BB] website</ref> ''Messenger of Allah'' was sponsored by the [[Kabaya|Kabaya Foods Corporation]]. The Kabayan Kingdom, His Imperial Highness Coconut and Mammy were named after the sponsor's products "Kabaya Caramel Coconut" and the "Mammy" brand bisquits from [[Morinaga & Company]].<ref name="全怪獣"/><ref name = "画報"/><ref name="60年代"/>

==Story==
The setting takes place in the fictional {{nihongo|Kabayan Kingdom|カバヤン王国|Kabayan Ōkoku}}, in the Middle East. [[Imperial Highness|His Imperial Highness]] Coconut, the heir to the throne, and his sister Mammy are searching for hidden treasure, guided by a map. When Coconut and Mammy are attacked by the {{nihongo|Crimson Lizard Gang|紅蜥蜴団|Kurenai Tokage-dan}}, the white turban-wearing ally of justice "Messenger of Allah" appears! Messenger of Allah's secret identity is Goro Narumi, a private investigator.

==Cast==
*[[Sonny Chiba|Shin'ichi Chiba]]: {{nihongo|Goro Narumi/Messenger of Allah|鳴海五郎 (なるみ ごろう)/アラーの使者|Narumi Goro/Arā no Shisha}}
*Kaneko Akio: {{nihongo|His Imperial Highness Coconut|ココナツ殿下|Kokonatsu Denka}}, successor of the Kabayan Kingdom.
*Yumi Ichijo: {{nihongo|Mammy|マミイ|Mamii}}, Coconut's sister.
*Hitoshi Ohmae: {{nihongo|Dr. Ijuin|伊集院博士|Ijuin Hakase}}
*Junorio Kozuka: {{nihongo|Dr. Ueda|上田博士|Ueda Hakase}}
*Arima Shinji: {{nihongo|Dr. Yamamura|山村博士|Yamamura Hakase}}
*Etsuko Sakurai: {{nihongo|Chikako Ueda|上田睦子|Ueda Chikako}}
*Koji Matsuyama: {{nihongo|Tamaran|タマラン|Tamaran}}

